---
import Crumb from "../components/Crumb.svelte";
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base>
    <h1>Welcome!</h1>
    <p>My name is E-Codz and I love hacking and tinkering with computers!</p>
    <p>I can program in JavaScript, Python and other tools which are listed down below, but i also like to self host on my
        own servers (e.g. with Raspberry Pis). I have some exprience with Arduinos, ESP32/ESP8266 too.
    </p>
    <p>I use these technologies in my "workflow":</p>
    <div id="crumbs">
        <Crumb client:only color="#ebd64d" icon="/img/javascript.jpg">
            JavaScript
        </Crumb>
        <Crumb client:only color="#689f63" icon="/img/node.svg">Node</Crumb>
        <Crumb client:only color="#5a9fd4" icon="/img/python.svg">Python</Crumb>
        <Crumb client:only color="#e33f8b" icon="/img/astro.svg">Astro</Crumb>
        <Crumb client:only color="#ff3e00" icon="/img/svelte.svg">Svelte </Crumb>
        <Crumb client:only color="#1793d1" icon="/img/archlinux.svg">
            Arch Linux
        </Crumb>
    </div>
</Base>

<style>
    #crumbs {
        display: flex;
        gap: 5px;
        overflow-y: auto;
        padding: 10px;
    } 
</style>
